aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].[Tags[?Key=='Name']|[0].Value, InstanceId, State.Name]" \
  --output table



To update your AWS CLI command to show all EC2 instances (regardless of state) along with their Name, Instance ID, and Instance State, use this:



✅ Output Explanation:
Tags[?Key=='Name']|[0].Value → Gets the instance's "Name" tag (if available).

InstanceId → Displays the instance ID.

State.Name → Shows the current state (e.g., running, stopped, pending, terminated).

Optional: Filter specific states
If you want only selected states (like running, stopped, pending, terminated), use:

aws ec2 describe-instances \
  --filters Name=instance-state-name,Values=running,stopped,pending,terminated \
  --query "Reservations[*].Instances[*].[Tags[?Key=='Name']|[0].Value, InstanceId, State.Name]" \
  --output table




